      "content": "Increasing your water intake might help with hydration, but it's not a guaranteed solution for the side effects you're experiencing. It's crucial to monitor your symptoms closely. If you're unable to keep food down, consider taking small sips of water throughout the day rather than large quantities all at once. Call your doctor to discuss these symptoms—they can provide more personalized advice or adjust your treatment plan accordingly. Remember, it's always better to be safe and seek professional advice rather than self-managing potentially serious side effects.",
      "source": "target",
